### 5.1 Key Data-Quality Findings (Hard-Won)

1. **The "100% barcode" claim was false.** Aldi `productId` is an internal article number (`solesta-sunflower-oil-...198481`); Iceland's is a URL slug. Neither is an EAN-8/13. **OFF barcode lookup does not work for Aldi/Iceland.** The sellable dataset must NOT advertise EAN coverage for these stores.
2. **OFF name-search returns garbage if ungated.** Early runs filled ingredients with French placeholder text (`une eau minérale naturelle`) by matching the wrong products. Precision gating is mandatory.
3. **Many "empty" fields are correct.** Single-ingredient products (oils, salts, plain milk, raw meat) have no rendered ingredients section. Empty is the right answer, not a bug.
4. **`allergens` should only ever be filled, never overwritten** — merge logic must respect existing scraped values.

