## 7. MVP Definition

### 7.1 Hacky test (validate demand)
List the cleanest sellable slice (Aldi + Iceland once enriched, or Tesco) as a downloadable dataset on Gumroad. Zero infrastructure. Measures whether anyone pays.

### 7.2 MCP — Minimum Compelling Product (first chargeable version)
- A clean, structured **UK grocery dataset** across ≥3 stores with honest field coverage and a per-product `data_quality_score`.
- Delivered as JSON + CSV with a documented schema and a quality report.
- Field list advertised **only where real** (no fake EAN claims).

### 7.3 v2+
- Live resolver **API** (the actual moat) with confidence scoring.
- Monthly refresh + versioning.
- White-label data feed and/or fintech partnership integrations.

### 7.4 Explicitly OUT of MVP scope
- Real-time price feeds (higher legal risk; sell nutrition/ingredients/allergens, not live prices).
- Full 5-store completeness before first revenue.
- Clustering/embedding infrastructure in the live path.

