## 10. Engineering Principles (Learned in Build)

- **Always test on a small sample (3–20) before a full run.** Identical output across "runs" = the edit never saved — verify the file on disk, don't trust the printout.
- **Precision over coverage** on every enrichment gate.
- **Fill empty fields only; never overwrite** existing scraped data.
- **Distinguish error from genuine miss** in logs (`fetch-failed` vs `no-confident-match`).
- **Reuse one browser instance**, close pages not the browser, checkpoint every N items, random delays.
- **Empty can be the correct answer** — single-ingredient products have no ingredient list.

